          "body": "The chapter's central pastoral provision is the promise of the *parakletos* (14:16, 26) — counselor, advocate, comforter. Jesus has been their *parakletos*; the Spirit will be *another* of the same kind. The Spirit will *abide with* the disciples and ultimately be *in* them (14:17) — anticipating Pentecost, when the indwelling becomes universal among believers. He will *teach* them all things (14:26) and *bring to remembrance* all Jesus said — the epistemological foundation of the apostolic witness that produced the New Testament. Jesus is not leaving His people resourceless; He is upgrading their access."
