          "title": "The cosmic backdrop — the ruler of this world",
          "body": "The chapter closes with the cross casting its shadow. *The ruler of this world is coming, and he has nothing in Me* (14:30) — Satan, working through Judas and the religious authorities and Pilate, has no purchase on Christ because Christ has no sin (cf. 2 Corinthians 5:21). The Son will die not because the enemy compels Him but *so that the world may know that I love the Father, I do exactly as the Father commanded Me* (14:31). The cross is the supreme act of filial obedience, deliberately undertaken for the world's witness. Then: *get up, let us go from here* — the chapter ends in motion, toward Gethsemane and Golgotha."
